A little hard to find (using Google maps) it's in the pedestrian way between Bishop Street and Fort Street Mall (which is also just a pedestrian street- fyi). So for driving it's between Bishop and Bethel at Hotel Street. Tacos are really good-- wish they were bigger! (Also wish they were double tortilla-Mexican style...) My wife loved the burrito, I thought it had too much sour cream & cheese... It's our second time coming tho- so they're doing something right!

I have been here countless time. They have the best prices in this island. The food is amazing as well! I have been a fan for 2 years now. Update from 4/20/2018: just stopped by to get some steak tacos and this time was outstanding. The crisp and smell from the tortilla are flavorful, which I never had before.  I think they just switched it up a little bit. My tortilla used to come out soft which is fine.  But the crispiness killed it! The steak has always been amazing. It gives you fantasy, especially when you are high. LOL!!!

This place is a hidden gem. We randomly found it while looking for a quick and easy bite to eat and were blown away by the tastiness and authenticity of the food here. Inexpensive ono Mexican food downtown. Salsa and chips for under $5 is a great side snack to the $2.50 tacos! Will be going back for more soon. I wish they had fish tacos though! Please get fish tacos if you are reading this :)

Saw all the yelp reviews & decided to try this place out. My boyfriend, son & I ordered 3 quesadillas (1 grilled steak & 2 grilled chicken) & they were amazing. It was worth every penny! On top of that, my bf decided to order 4 tacos on the side before we left lol.  Location-wise: Convenient, hard to find parking but it'a worth the trip Pros: My son hates veggies, but he actually ate a lot. That's saying something! He loved it! Cons: None  If you're ever on China-town side, hit this place up! No regrets!
